Several changes in leadership occurred during this period. On 12 April, President Roosevelt died and was succeeded by Harry S. Truman. Benito Mussolini was killed by Italian partisans on 28 April.[277] Two days later, Hitler committed suicide in besieged Berlin, and he was succeeded by Grand Admiral Karl Dönitz.[278]
Total and unconditional surrender in Europe was signed on 7 and 8 May, to be effective by the end of 8 May.[279] German Army Group Centre resisted in Prague until 11 May.[280]
